SIMPLE: wrecker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wrecker
<hw>Wreck"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
causes a wreck, as by false lights, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who searches fro, or works upon, the wrecks of
vessels, etc. Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> One who visits a wreck for the
purpose of plunder. <sd>(b)</sd> One who is employed in saving property
or lives from a wrecked vessel, or in saving the vessel; <as>as, the
<ex>wreckers</ex> of Key West</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A vessel employed by wreckers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wreckfish</ent>⟦br⟧
